This holiday season, I’m supporting @coreresponse for their ongoing emergency relief efforts across the world. Their teams on the ground in Haiti, Ukraine, Pakistan, Brazil, throughout the US, and more are supporting the hardest hit communities with relief that addresses their most critical needs. Please #donate if you can at coreresponse.org/giving-season 

These folks do REAL boots on the ground work and I’ve been a fan of them for a long time. Looking forward to working more closely @coreresponse @seanpenn

Loved this chat so much. I definitely don’t have it all figured out but I think the key to life for me is just to keep on growing and trying to make that 12 year old self of mine proud. 

I love acting, writing, producing and I’ll do it forever. I love writing music and I’ll do it as long as the fans will have me. Whether it’s a small bar or a big stage, it’s the love of it that keeps me going. Thank you to Canadian radio for blasting these songs. It’s surreal and didn’t expect any of this. Debut album highway 99 is on all streaming platforms now so check it out and let me know what you think (if you got a little country in you. 

Also we’re playing an acoustic set on @goodmorningamerica stage tmr if anyones up and wants to tune in.

Vacations are great, but do you know what’s even greater? Building a life that you don’t need to escape from.

The best vacations, Marcus Aurelius writes in Meditations, require no vacating. 

“People look for retreats for themselves in the country, by the coast, or in the hills,” Marcus wrote. “There is nowhere that a person can find a more peaceful and trouble-free retreat than in his own mind…So constantly give yourself this retreat, and renew yourself.” 

Listen to the full episode with @alexanderludwig and @ryanholiday on The @dailystoic Podcast.
